# Backend Engineering (NestJS)

Stack: NestJS modular monolith in `apps/api/`. See `Docs/07-repository-and-application-architecture.md`.

## Module Structure

```text
apps/api/src/modules/<feature>/
  <feature>.module.ts
  <feature>.controller.ts   # thin — delegate only
  <feature>.service.ts      # business logic
  <feature>.repository.ts   # data access
  dto/
  entities/ or schemas/
```

## Conventions

- Use **dependency injection** — inject services and repositories via constructor.
- Controllers: validate DTOs, call service, map response — no business logic.
- Services: orchestration, authorization checks, domain rules.
- Repositories: MongoDB queries only — no business rules.
- Use `packages/types` for shared DTOs/types consumed by frontends.
- Global exception filters and structured logging for errors.
- Health check at `/health` for load balancers.

## API Design

- RESTful resources with consistent naming (`/api/v1/...`).
- Return appropriate HTTP status codes and error shapes.
- Paginate list endpoints; document auth requirements.
- Stream AI responses via SSE where applicable.

## Do Not

- Put business logic in controllers or repositories.
- Call OpenAI or external AI APIs directly from controllers.
- Bypass the auth module for protected routes.
